ial networks that consume their kids -- by, for example, taking the time to navigate Snapchat and Instagram -- so they can discuss them in a way that makes them sound informed rather than out of touch. ","note":"Catherine Steiner-Adair, with Teresa H. Barker\r\nHarper Collins, 2013 ","link_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Big-Disconnect-Protecting-Childhood-Relationships/dp/0062082434/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*American Girls: Social Media and the Secret Lives of Teenagers*","blurb":"Sales visited hundreds of girls around the United States as they lived their lives, tracking their interactions with the digital world. *American Girls* is entertaining and vivid but also disturbing for what it tells us about how teen girls are shaped by the time they spend immersed in social networks.","note":"Nancy Jo Sales\r\nAlfred A. Knopf, 2016  ","link_url":"https://www.amazon.com/American-Girls-Social-Secret-Teenagers/dp/0804173184/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*Last Child in the Woods: Saving Our Children from Nature Deficit Disorder*","blurb":"Louv won the Audubon Medal for this illuminating book on the role of nature in promoting healthy childhood development. As Louv described it, nature is a powerful antidote to the screen world (and to many other maladies, from obesity and attention disorders to depression and anxiety).","note":"Richard Louv\r\nAlgonquin Books, 2005","link_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Last-Child-Woods-Children-Nature-Deficit/dp/156512605X/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*Addiction by Design: Machine Gambling in Las Vegas*"